End Process

@Reasoning:
Verifies comma-separated selector lists. The parser must produce a
selector group node rather than treating ", h2, h3" as part of the
first selector's identifier.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Increment total. Use the static literal "h1, h2, h3 { margin: 0; }".
Translator with 0 options. Branch on hir != 0.
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- Input "h1, h2, h3 { margin: 0; }" -> non-null HIR with a selector
  group, passed += 1
- Translator coalesces the three selectors into one identifier or
  fails -> failed += 1
@End TestCases

