End Process

@Reasoning:
Verifies a non-nested at-rule (@import) translates correctly. At-rules
have a different grammar from regular declarations and use url() function
notation, both of which the lexer must handle.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Increment total. Use the static literal "@import url(\"test.css\");".
Translator with 0 options. Branch on hir != 0.
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- Input @import url("test.css"); -> non-null HIR, passed += 1
- url() function not recognized or @ token mishandled -> failed += 1
@End TestCases

Process called "test_at_rule" takes results as Integer returns Integer:
    Let _rtot1 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with results, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with results, 0, _rtot1 plus 1

    Let source be "@import url(\"test.css\");"
