@Reasoning:
Verifies a standalone /* ... */ CSS comment translates without error.
The translator may either preserve or drop the comment, but it must not
fail. Confirms the lexer correctly skips the multi-character /* ... */
sentinel rather than treating "/" or "*" as a stray token.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Increment total. Use the static literal "/* Comment */". Translator with
0 options. Branch on hir != 0.
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- Input "/* Comment */" -> non-null HIR (whether comment is preserved
  or stripped is up to the translator), passed += 1
- Lexer fails on /* -> translator returns 0 -> failed += 1
@End TestCases

Process called "test_comment" takes results as Integer returns Integer:
    Let _rtot1 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with results, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with results, 0, _rtot1 plus 1

    Let source be "/* Comment */"
    Let hir be proc translate_css_to_hir from Translator with source, 0

    If hir is not equal to 0:
        proc print_test_success with "Comment"
        Let _rpas1 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with results, 8
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with results, 8, _rpas1 plus 1
        Return 1
    End If

    proc print_test_failure with "Comment: failed"
    Let _rfal1 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with results, 16
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with results, 16, _rfal1 plus 1

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Verifies the single-colon pseudo-class form. The lexer must produce a
pseudo-class token when ":hover" follows an identifier without
whitespace; failure here means selector lexing is too aggressive at
splitting tokens.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Increment total. Use the static literal "a:hover { color: blue; }".
Translator with 0 options. Branch on hir != 0.
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- Input "a:hover { color: blue; }" -> non-null HIR with pseudo-class
  selector, passed += 1
- Lexer treats ":hover" as ":" then identifier -> translator may still
  succeed but selector semantics wrong; null HIR -> failed += 1
@End TestCases

Process called "test_pseudo_class" takes results as Integer returns Integer:
    Let _rtot1 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with results, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with results, 0, _rtot1 plus 1

    Let source be "a:hover { color: blue; }"
    Let hir be proc translate_css_to_hir from Translator with source, 0

    If hir is not equal to 0:
        proc print_test_success with "Pseudo-class"
        Let _rpas1 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with results, 8
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with results, 8, _rpas1 plus 1
        Return 1
    End If

    proc print_test_failure with "Pseudo-class: failed"
    Let _rfal1 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with results, 16
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with results, 16, _rfal1 plus 1

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Verifies attribute selectors with [name="value"] syntax. Catches a
regression where the lexer treats "[" as an unrecognized token or the
parser fails to consume the matching "]", which would silently corrupt
the selector AST and cause downstream emitter problems.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Increment total. Use the static literal
"input[type=\"text\"] { border: 1px solid #ccc; }".
Translator with 0 options. Branch on hir != 0.
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- Input "input[type=\"text\"] { border: 1px solid #ccc; }" -> non-null
  HIR with attribute-selector node, passed += 1
- Lexer breaks on "[" or "=" inside selector -> translator returns 0
  -> failed += 1
@End TestCases

