End Process

@Reasoning:
Banner emitted once at startup. Separator width (35 "=") matches the
title length so the heading boxes cleanly in CI logs.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Emit the title and the "=" rule via display_string (each on its own
line). Always returns 1.
@End Implementation

Process called "print_header" returns Integer:
    proc display_string with "CSS to HIR Translation Test Suite"
    proc display_string with "==================================="

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
"[PASS] <name>" line shared by all 10 test_* procs in this file.
Centralized so the formatting is identical across the suite.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Emit "[PASS] " prefix with display_string_continuing (no newline), then
the caller-owned test_name with display_string (terminates the line).
@End Implementation

Process called "print_test_success" takes test_name as Integer returns Integer:
    proc display_string_continuing with "[PASS] "
    proc display_string with test_name

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
"[FAIL] <name>" line. Unlike the parser/round-trip suites this signature
takes only a name because each test_* proc here passes a pre-formatted
"<scenario>: failed" string, so the reason is baked into the name.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Emit "[FAIL] " prefix with display_string_continuing (no newline), then
the caller-owned test_name with display_string (terminates the line).
@End Implementation

Process called "print_test_failure" takes test_name as Integer returns Integer:
    proc display_string_continuing with "[FAIL] "
    proc display_string with test_name

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Final summary block matching peer CSS suites. Reads counters through
type-checked struct field access (results.total etc.) at the report
site even though the hot path in each test_* proc uses raw
memory_get_int64 mutations.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Print "=" separator, "Test Results:" heading, then Total/Passed/Failed
lines via display_string_continuing for labels and display_integer for
the counter values.
@End Implementation

Process called "print_results" takes results as Integer returns Integer:
    proc display_string with "==================================="
    proc display_string with "Test Results:"

    proc display_string_continuing with "Total: "
    proc display_integer with results.total

    proc display_string_continuing with "Passed: "
    proc display_integer with results.passed

    proc display_string_continuing with "Failed: "
    proc display_integer with results.failed

    Return 1
End Process

Note: End of CSS to HIR Translation Test Suite
